items.title: Mob burns Nigerian woman to death for alleged blasphemy
items.description: Police have condemned the killing as "jungle justice" vowing to bring the perpetrators to justice.

items.title: UN chief demands release of 11 staff arrested in Yemen
items.description: The food and children's agency workers are the latest UN staff detained by Houthi authorities.

items.title: Judge blocks Trump administration move to deport Guatemalan children
items.description: Advocacy groups sought emergency action amid reports planes carrying the children were about to take off.

items.title: Putin says he reached 'understandings' with Trump over end of Ukraine war
items.description: The Russian president also defended his decision to invade Ukraine, once again blaming the war on the West.

items.title: Fugitive wanted over Australia police killings being helped, police say
items.description: Dezi Freeman vanished into thick bushland after killing two police officers and hasn't been seen since.
